			<ns0:name>s...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/108394971971967673680/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">In the design for the ARM sandbox we added a sequence that should work better on pipelined implementations.  That is, rather than using BIC to clear the bits on the address for a load or store, we use compute a predicate for the load or store using a TST to check whether the address lies within the sandbox.  This sequence was implemented in
lib/Target/ARM/ARMNaClRewritePass.cpp.  It had to be turned off, however, because sometimes CPSRLive was being set incorrectly.  When I analyzed what is going on, it turns out that we were not computing liveness correctly for CPSR.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-12-03T22:48:49.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2012-05-30T21:39:04.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Assigned</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
